      section
        .row
          br
          .page-header
            h1 Converting from JSON to YAML
        .row
          .span12
            p Converting JSON to YAML is a two part process.
            p.
              First you have to convert a string of JSON into an object in whichever language you're using.
              This process is referred to as to <strong>parse</strong> or to <strong>deserialize</strong>.
            p.
              Next you'll need to convert that object into a YAML string.
              This process is referred to as to to <strong>emit</strong>,
              to <strong>serialize</strong>, or to <strong>stringify</strong>.
            p.
              Technically speaking, JSON already is YAML since YAML allows for the use
              of brackets and commas in the exact same way that JSON does.
              However, for the sake of human-readability, it's very convenient to use
              the whitespace syntax of YAML without any brackets.
